Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c\n+++ b/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c\n@@ -4249,7 +4249,13 @@\n     GET_REFLECTION_OBJECT_PTR(ce);\n-    _class_string(&str, ce, &intern->obj, "");\n+    if (Z_TYPE(intern->obj) == IS_OBJECT) {\n+        _class_string(&str, ce, &intern->obj, "");\n+    } else {\n+        _class_string(&str, ce, NULL, "");\n+    }\n     RETURN_STR(smart_str_extract(&str));\n }\n /* }}} */\n'}`
responded: The vulnerability is a segmentation fault caused by a dereference of an invalid or unallocated memory address, specifically in `_class_string` at `ext/reflection/php_reflection.c:481:22`, called from `zim_ReflectionClass___toString` at line 4250.

From the code, the function:
```c
ZEND_METHOD(ReflectionClass, __toString)
{
    reflection_object *intern;
    zend_class_entry *ce;
    smart_str str = {0};

    if (zend_parse_parameters_none() == FAILURE) {
        RETURN_THROWS();
    }
    GET_REFLECTION_OBJECT_PTR(ce);
    _class_string(&str, ce, &intern->obj, "");
    RETURN_STR(smart_str_extract(&str));
}
```
`GET_REFLECTION_OBJECT_PTR(ce)` macro sets `ce = intern->ptr` after checking `intern->ptr != NULL`, but it does **not** check if `intern->obj` is a valid object or initialized. If `intern->obj` is uninitialized or not an object, passing `&intern->obj` to `_class_string` can cause a segfault when `_class_string` dereferences it (e.g., `Z_TYPE_P(obj)`).

**Patch Plan:**
- Add a check before calling `_class_string` to ensure `intern->obj` is a valid object (i.e., `Z_TYPE(intern->obj) == IS_OBJECT`).
- If not, pass `NULL` as the `obj` argument to `_class_string`.

This will prevent invalid dereference in `_class_string`.

Now, let's generate the patch.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c b/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c
index f24b00a2857..4df84e248e9 100644
--- a/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c
+++ b/ext/reflection/php_reflection.c
@@ -4247,7 +4247,11 @@ ZEND_METHOD(ReflectionClass, __toString)
 		RETURN_THROWS();
 	}
 	GET_REFLECTION_OBJECT_PTR(ce);
-	_class_string(&str, ce, &intern->obj, "");
+    if (Z_TYPE(intern->obj) == IS_OBJECT) {
+        _class_string(&str, ce, &intern->obj, "");
+    } else {
+        _class_string(&str, ce, NULL, "");
+    }
 	RETURN_STR(smart_str_extract(&str));
 }
 /* }}} */

